1
00:02:00,570 --> 00:02:20,570
RSG Release Team

2
00:02:34,571 --> 00:02:35,697
Wait...

3
00:02:35,739 --> 00:02:36,698
Later!

4
00:02:38,533 --> 00:02:39,993
Careful, it'll get crumpled.

5
00:02:40,076 --> 00:02:41,745
Just hold your arm straight.

6
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:52,255
And now...

7
00:02:52,672 --> 00:03:00,221
Here are the candidates in the
talent portion of the competition.

8
00:03:00,555 --> 00:03:02,891
And our first candidate for today is...

9
00:03:03,183 --> 00:03:05,769
Arlina Delos Santos!

10
00:03:17,781 --> 00:03:18,823
Excuse me...

11
00:03:18,865 --> 00:03:19,783
Excuse me...

12
00:03:22,535 --> 00:03:23,828
Have a drink.

13
00:03:27,290 --> 00:03:28,583
Don't be nervous.

14
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:31,586
Remember, just keep on going.

15
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:33,713
We're here to have fun.

16
00:03:35,382 --> 00:03:39,928
Remember, it's what's inside
you that counts, okay?

17
00:03:39,969 --> 00:03:41,680
Not your looks.

18
00:03:41,721 --> 00:03:42,681
Alright.

19
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:43,807
Go for it!

20
00:03:43,848 --> 00:03:45,266
Yes, Mommy.

21
00:03:45,308 --> 00:03:48,728
Ma'am, my child is ready!
She'll join and sing now.

22
00:03:49,562 --> 00:03:50,855
Just stay over there.

23
00:03:50,897 --> 00:03:52,065
I'll call you when it's her turn.

24
00:03:52,107 --> 00:03:54,150
Stop touching that! For crying out loud!

25
00:03:54,192 --> 00:03:56,361
That gown cost me 2,000 pesos!
So, you better win.

26
00:03:56,403 --> 00:03:58,279
Beat all those other kids!

27
00:03:58,571 --> 00:04:01,700
And the next one to present her talent,

28
00:04:01,741 --> 00:04:04,119
is candidate number 7.

29
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:09,624
She belongs to section Pussycat
under Miss Maglinao's kinder class.

30
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:11,418
She's 7 years old.

31
00:04:11,835 --> 00:04:13,795
And her favorite subject is...

32
00:04:14,045 --> 00:04:15,088
Wow! Math!

33
00:04:15,463 --> 00:04:16,715
Here she is...

34
00:04:17,007 --> 00:04:21,344
Maria Nathalia Bustamante Gascon.

35
00:04:25,140 --> 00:04:28,351
Mommy's tummy was big and round!

36
00:04:28,810 --> 00:04:31,813
What's that?! My brother Ojie pondered.

37
00:04:31,855 --> 00:04:34,774
A ball? A basketball?

38
00:04:34,816 --> 00:04:36,818
No, it's something else.

39
00:04:36,860 --> 00:04:38,486
Maybe a little toy?

40
00:04:38,528 --> 00:04:40,530
No, it's a bundle of joy.

41
00:04:41,406 --> 00:04:44,284
What's inside, Mommy?

42
00:04:44,325 --> 00:04:46,369
A surprise I offer.

43
00:04:46,953 --> 00:04:50,331
The surprise turned out to be me!

44
00:04:52,167 --> 00:04:55,337
How could the ball become a baby?

45
00:04:56,254 --> 00:04:58,006
Mother breaks into joyous laughter.

46
00:04:58,048 --> 00:04:59,299
When you grow a little older...

47
00:04:59,341 --> 00:05:00,800
You will surely discover.

48
00:05:05,930 --> 00:05:07,015
You taught her all that?

49
00:05:07,057 --> 00:05:08,933
My goodness, that will never win!

50
00:05:09,851 --> 00:05:12,437
Hurry up, they're lining up
for the graduation march.

51
00:05:12,479 --> 00:05:13,438
What's wrong?

52
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:15,106
She wants to join the other kids now.

53
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:16,608
Finally! Then, hurry up.

54
00:05:16,649 --> 00:05:17,817
Let's go, they're about to march.

55
00:05:17,859 --> 00:05:18,693
How about you guys?

56
00:05:18,735 --> 00:05:20,111
Hurry now!

57
00:05:20,528 --> 00:05:22,614
You should have recited another piece.

58
00:05:22,655 --> 00:05:24,574
Because you'll never win with that.

59
00:05:25,992 --> 00:05:27,702
It's not a big deal if you don't make it.

60
00:05:27,744 --> 00:05:29,621
This isn't about looks anyway.

61
00:05:30,330 --> 00:05:34,292
Then why the heck join a beauty contest
if you're not being judged for your beauty?

62
00:05:35,085 --> 00:05:36,211
Brother!

63
00:05:36,252 --> 00:05:38,963
Give me that cap so I can finally graduate.

64
00:06:00,151 --> 00:06:07,033
Here are the judges' decision
for our Miss Kindergarten contest...

65
00:06:07,075 --> 00:06:09,869
Let's start with our special awards.

66
00:06:09,911 --> 00:06:14,666
The judges have chosen the
Best in Costume and Miss Talent.

67
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:18,712
And the special award
for Best in Costume goes to...

68
00:06:18,753 --> 00:06:20,255
Stop complaining.

69
00:06:20,296 --> 00:06:22,966
From Section Elephant under Ms. Zenaida Mendoza...

70
00:06:23,008 --> 00:06:27,178
Candidate number 1, Arlina Delos Santos.

71
00:06:32,225 --> 00:06:37,564
And the Ms. Talent awardee comes from
Section Giraffe under Ms. Louie Cruz...

72
00:06:37,605 --> 00:06:40,066
- Candidate number 4...
- That must be your lousy poem.

73
00:06:40,108 --> 00:06:41,860
Erika Guevara!

74
00:06:48,908 --> 00:06:50,785
And now ladies and gentlemen...

75
00:06:51,161 --> 00:06:55,290
The winner of the much awaited Ms. Kinder award...

76
00:06:56,416 --> 00:06:58,543
She comes from Section Pussycat.

77
00:06:58,585 --> 00:07:00,503
I'm sure you already know who she is!

78
00:07:01,379 --> 00:07:03,006
Candidate number 7.

79
00:07:03,506 --> 00:07:06,134
Maria Nathalia Bustamante Gascon!

80
00:07:08,511 --> 00:07:11,389
Okay! You did great!

81
00:07:12,807 --> 00:07:14,976
Yes! Yes!

82
00:07:15,894 --> 00:07:16,853
Give me that.

83
00:07:26,112 --> 00:07:29,824
Believe it or not, Maya won by unanimous decision.

84
00:07:31,910 --> 00:07:35,205
She really stood out among the other candidates.

85
00:07:35,246 --> 00:07:38,583
- Ding, get the sauce for that.
- Sure, there's some over there.

86
00:07:38,625 --> 00:07:39,501
I'll get the hotdogs.

87
00:07:39,542 --> 00:07:40,877
Excuse me.

88
00:07:43,380 --> 00:07:44,964
Mom, my friends.

89
00:07:45,006 --> 00:07:47,550
Give them something to eat. Feel at home, okay?

90
00:07:47,592 --> 00:07:49,386
Find a spot outside, okay?

91
00:07:49,969 --> 00:07:51,930
Can you bring this outside for the kids?
Give me that.

92
00:07:51,971 --> 00:07:53,223
- I'll take care of this.
- Okay.

93
00:07:54,265 --> 00:07:55,684
As I was saying...

94
00:07:56,643 --> 00:08:00,397
My mother and my brother's father got married.

95
00:08:00,438 --> 00:08:02,315
Then they split up.

96
00:08:02,691 --> 00:08:04,734
My gosh Maya, that's bad!

97
00:08:04,776 --> 00:08:10,990
My mother says when God joins two people together,
no one can break them apart.

98
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:13,118
How did God get in the picture?

99
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:16,204
Because it's God who marries people.

100
00:08:16,287 --> 00:08:17,205
That isn't true!

101
00:08:17,288 --> 00:08:21,042
My mother and her husband
were married by a town mayor.

102
00:08:21,084 --> 00:08:24,629
The mayor of Abucay. You can even ask my father.

103
00:08:24,671 --> 00:08:25,839
Dad!

104
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:30,760
Mom and Ojie's father were married
by the mayor of Abucay right?

105
00:08:30,802 --> 00:08:31,720
Maya!

106
00:08:32,470 --> 00:08:37,517
I want to sponsor Maya in the
Johnson & Johnson's search for the

107
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:40,186
Prince and Princess of Manila 1998!

108
00:08:40,228 --> 00:08:42,147
- This is a huge deal!
- There's no more ice cream, Mom!

109
00:08:42,188 --> 00:08:43,773
- You'll get a lot of money!
- I already called the store.

110
00:08:43,815 --> 00:08:45,483
- There's a cash prize!
- But that takes time!

111
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:47,068
- The ice cream will come!
- There's an educational plan!

112
00:08:49,779 --> 00:08:51,948
So young and you're already spreading gossip.

113
00:08:51,990 --> 00:08:54,617
But, I'm just telling the truth!

114
00:08:54,659 --> 00:08:57,620
Still, there are things that
you can't tell other peope!

115
00:08:58,038 --> 00:08:58,955
You must be ashamed!

116
00:08:58,997 --> 00:09:01,541
Mommy said you shouldn't be ashamed of the truth.

117
00:09:01,583 --> 00:09:03,084
What if you stole something,
won't you be ashamed of it?

118
00:09:03,126 --> 00:09:06,338
Mommy said, you should never do what is shameful!

119
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:07,380
Ding!

120
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:10,759
Ding!

121
00:09:11,634 --> 00:09:14,179
Your mother's on the phone. She's raving mad.

122
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:16,014
Maya, be careful!

123
00:09:24,314 --> 00:09:26,024
Let me continue...

124
00:09:26,066 --> 00:09:28,193
For crying out loud, stop it!

125
00:09:29,319 --> 00:09:31,279
So to continue my story...

126
00:09:31,321 --> 00:09:35,075
- My mother and my brother's father split up.
- Hello, Ma?

127
00:09:35,283 --> 00:09:36,242
After that...

128
00:09:36,284 --> 00:09:39,662
my mother and my father...

129
00:09:39,704 --> 00:09:40,955
became like this.

130
00:09:40,997 --> 00:09:41,831
Married?

131
00:09:41,873 --> 00:09:44,292
That can't be! She's already married.

132
00:09:44,334 --> 00:09:46,002
Not married!

133
00:09:46,044 --> 00:09:47,045
They're just real tight.

134
00:09:47,087 --> 00:09:49,130
As my father's mother would say...

135
00:09:49,381 --> 00:09:51,466
Married only in bed!

136
00:09:51,508 --> 00:09:52,467
Maya!

137
00:10:38,096 --> 00:10:39,931
Mother wants me to come home.

138
00:10:43,476 --> 00:10:49,190
She's going out of town
to look for maids for her agency.

139
00:10:49,649 --> 00:10:51,526
No one will be at the house.

140
00:10:55,447 --> 00:10:56,614
Don't get mad.

141
00:11:04,247 --> 00:11:06,708
Every single time my mother needs me,
you get mad.

142
00:11:08,376 --> 00:11:10,337
I'm not angry! See?

143
00:11:12,005 --> 00:11:13,381
That wasn't an angry face!

144
00:11:13,631 --> 00:11:15,050
I'm actually really happy.

145
00:11:16,509 --> 00:11:18,970
You get mad everytime she calls me.

146
00:11:20,722 --> 00:11:21,723
That's not the point.

147
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:26,102
Your mother calling you doesn't make me angry.

148
00:11:27,062 --> 00:11:30,565
I get angry because she's doing this to prove

149
00:11:30,607 --> 00:11:32,776
that you're at her beck and call.

150
00:11:32,859 --> 00:11:36,154
And I can't do anything about it
because we aren't married.

151
00:11:41,951 --> 00:11:42,911
So...

152
00:11:43,745 --> 00:11:44,996
What can you say?

153
00:11:46,998 --> 00:11:48,124
I gotta go.

154
00:11:49,209 --> 00:11:50,460
See you when I see you!

155
00:11:52,587 --> 00:11:53,380
Well...

156
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:55,799
See yours when I see yours!

157
00:12:00,929 --> 00:12:06,142
All the kids I know only have
one father even if they have 10 siblings!

158
00:12:06,685 --> 00:12:08,520
Shouldn't it be that way, Mom?

159
00:12:08,561 --> 00:12:10,271
Not always.

160
00:12:10,647 --> 00:12:12,732
Sometimes, couples break up.

161
00:12:12,774 --> 00:12:15,151
Especially if they fight all the time.

162
00:12:15,193 --> 00:12:18,196
Did you and dad fight all the time?

163
00:12:20,990 --> 00:12:22,367
The truth is...

164
00:12:23,326 --> 00:12:24,452
Your father and I?

165
00:12:25,912 --> 00:12:26,913
No!

166
00:12:27,747 --> 00:12:29,582
Then why?

167
00:12:30,041 --> 00:12:32,377
Because your father was offered a job in Surigao.

168
00:12:32,419 --> 00:12:36,089
He was the senior technician
in a mining company.

169
00:12:36,131 --> 00:12:38,425
I didn't go because I had a job here.

170
00:12:40,051 --> 00:12:43,013
Was your job more important than my father?

171
00:12:49,853 --> 00:12:52,689
I wanted to make something of myself, too.

172
00:12:53,231 --> 00:12:55,442
I have my own dreams.

173
00:12:57,318 --> 00:12:58,778
I don't get it.

174
00:12:59,154 --> 00:13:01,197
It's easy, listen...

175
00:13:01,698 --> 00:13:03,366
I'm your mother.

176
00:13:04,075 --> 00:13:05,910
You love me very much.

177
00:13:06,453 --> 00:13:09,748
But you wouldn't like it if I said to you:

178
00:13:09,789 --> 00:13:12,625
"Ojie, you can only love me."

179
00:13:12,917 --> 00:13:14,419
Or "Stop going to school."

180
00:13:14,461 --> 00:13:18,089
Or "Ojie, you can't be with
your friends because I'd be alone."

181
00:13:19,799 --> 00:13:21,343
Would you like that?

182
00:13:21,384 --> 00:13:22,886
Of course not!

183
00:13:23,345 --> 00:13:24,763
What about me?

184
00:13:24,804 --> 00:13:27,682
Precisely! What about you?

185
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:30,352
It's the same with married people.

186
00:13:30,393 --> 00:13:32,604
As much as they love each other...

187
00:13:32,645 --> 00:13:35,857
they have to think of themselves, too.

188
00:13:39,736 --> 00:13:42,155
Don't you love him anymore?

189
00:13:42,197 --> 00:13:43,823
Fool!

190
00:13:44,616 --> 00:13:46,409
Of course I do!

191
00:13:46,951 --> 00:13:49,245
I love Raffy, your father.

192
00:13:50,038 --> 00:13:51,998
I love Ding as well.

193
00:13:52,957 --> 00:13:55,710
It's not easy to understand...

194
00:13:56,544 --> 00:13:58,588
Because sometimes...

195
00:13:59,339 --> 00:14:00,882
Sometimes, when...

196
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:05,303
It's just the way it is.

197
00:14:05,804 --> 00:14:07,222
It's just how it is?

198
00:14:07,263 --> 00:14:08,973
Do you understand now?

199
00:14:09,224 --> 00:14:10,809
No, I still can't.

200
00:14:13,645 --> 00:14:15,814
I was so shocked.

201
00:14:16,690 --> 00:14:20,735
I froze in fear. I couldn't even move.

202
00:14:21,736 --> 00:14:24,572
I could smell gasoline all over my body.

203
00:14:25,740 --> 00:14:28,952
Then, he lit the match.

204
00:14:31,121 --> 00:14:34,749
His eyes turned wild, like the devil himself.

205
00:14:35,291 --> 00:14:36,835
He said to me,

206
00:14:37,544 --> 00:14:41,297
"You thought, I couldn't do this?"

207
00:14:45,010 --> 00:14:48,388
And that lit match...

208
00:14:49,055 --> 00:14:50,932
He threw it at me!

209
00:14:50,974 --> 00:14:53,018
My whole body went up in flames.

210
00:14:54,227 --> 00:14:57,772
Until now, I still can't believe he did this to me.

211
00:15:04,279 --> 00:15:07,407
I can't go with you.
There's no one with the children.

212
00:15:08,158 --> 00:15:10,618
I asked my neighbor to keep an eye on them.

213
00:15:19,127 --> 00:15:21,212
The woman called again.

214
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:24,382
The one who just keeps crying?

215
00:15:24,424 --> 00:15:26,634
Yes, she's driving me crazy!

216
00:15:29,596 --> 00:15:31,222
Are you alone?

217
00:15:32,182 --> 00:15:34,517
No one lobbies in the Senate alone.

218
00:15:34,559 --> 00:15:36,269
Everybody will be there.

219
00:15:37,145 --> 00:15:40,023
What about Soledad Gatdula's case?

220
00:15:40,106 --> 00:15:41,941
The migrant is now handling it.

221
00:15:41,983 --> 00:15:44,235
They'll get the body repatriated.

222
00:15:46,404 --> 00:15:48,740
Alright, I have to go.

223
00:15:48,782 --> 00:15:50,241
See you when I see you!

224
00:15:50,992 --> 00:15:52,410
Well...

225
00:16:10,387 --> 00:16:12,013
What time did he arrive?

226
00:16:14,808 --> 00:16:16,893
So, that means I can stay here a bit longer?

227
00:16:18,186 --> 00:16:20,605
Your brother, is he home?

228
00:16:22,607 --> 00:16:23,900
No, nevermind.

229
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:29,739
If I talk to your father,
he'd think I have a crush on him.

230
00:16:30,657 --> 00:16:32,659
Alright darling, okay.

231
00:16:36,037 --> 00:16:36,788
Hi.

232
00:16:38,748 --> 00:16:40,458
Do you still remember me?

233
00:16:41,584 --> 00:16:43,253
I'm back here in Manila.

234
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:45,255
How are you?

235
00:16:46,381 --> 00:16:49,217
My brother told me you'd be here.

236
00:17:06,943 --> 00:17:08,528
How's Ojie?

237
00:17:09,404 --> 00:17:12,032
He's all grown up!

238
00:17:13,366 --> 00:17:14,951
In fact, he's already circumcised.

239
00:17:16,828 --> 00:17:20,665
I can't tell if he's a grown up or still my baby.

240
00:17:20,957 --> 00:17:24,294
He's already courting girls
but sometimes he acts like a child.

241
00:17:24,711 --> 00:17:26,171
You must have spoiled him.

242
00:17:26,212 --> 00:17:27,213
A bit.

243
00:17:28,465 --> 00:17:30,091
I let him have his way.

244
00:17:36,681 --> 00:17:38,808
Can I see Ojie?

245
00:17:41,186 --> 00:17:42,479
Why not?

246
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:44,856
When do you want to?

247
00:17:45,732 --> 00:17:47,025
Tomorrow?

248
00:17:48,068 --> 00:17:50,528
It's up to you. Where?

249
00:17:50,570 --> 00:17:52,447
It's up to you.

250
00:17:52,739 --> 00:17:54,199
What time?

251
00:17:55,742 --> 00:17:56,743
It's up to you.

252
00:18:03,708 --> 00:18:04,876
Why don't...

253
00:18:04,918 --> 00:18:06,294
you find yourself...

254
00:18:06,836 --> 00:18:08,254
a spouse as well, Raffy?

255
00:18:08,630 --> 00:18:11,299
It's been a long time since we were together.

256
00:18:11,341 --> 00:18:12,676
I have.

257
00:18:13,343 --> 00:18:15,136
It's been a year.

258
00:18:16,304 --> 00:18:17,764
She's pregnant now.

259
00:18:17,806 --> 00:18:19,891
I'll become a father again.

260
00:18:24,437 --> 00:18:25,897
You must be happy, huh?

261
00:18:25,939 --> 00:18:28,566
Mom, are you sure he's Ojie's father?

262
00:18:28,608 --> 00:18:29,984
Why, of course!

263
00:18:32,028 --> 00:18:33,113
Ding...

264
00:18:33,154 --> 00:18:35,240
It's not like we're checking in a motel!

265
00:18:35,281 --> 00:18:37,784
We aren't doing anything wrong.

266
00:18:38,326 --> 00:18:39,536
Is that so?

267
00:18:40,453 --> 00:18:41,579
Mom...

268
00:18:41,621 --> 00:18:44,582
Will you still recognize Ojie's father?

269
00:18:44,624 --> 00:18:46,209
Of course. Your mother's still in love with him!

270
00:18:46,251 --> 00:18:48,670
Of course I do. He's my friend!

271
00:18:48,712 --> 00:18:52,298
Just your friend? Mom, he's my father!

272
00:18:52,340 --> 00:18:53,675
He's your husband!

273
00:18:53,717 --> 00:18:54,592
Fool!

274
00:18:54,634 --> 00:18:57,053
Mom's real husband is my father!

275
00:18:57,137 --> 00:19:01,641
No way, silly! My father is mom's real husband!

276
00:19:01,850 --> 00:19:04,436
Fine, they're both my husbands!

277
00:19:04,477 --> 00:19:05,812
Two husbands?

278
00:19:07,063 --> 00:19:09,399
Elizabeth Taylor had seven!

279
00:19:10,316 --> 00:19:11,317
Hey!

280
00:19:11,776 --> 00:19:13,236
You're not Elizabeth Taylor!

281
00:19:14,029 --> 00:19:16,573
Oh, this isn't going anywhere.

282
00:19:16,614 --> 00:19:18,825
Ojie, eat your dinner. You have to be up early.

283
00:19:18,867 --> 00:19:21,661
I'll also have dinner now. I'm going with you.

284
00:19:22,162 --> 00:19:23,621
Right! Go with them!

285
00:19:24,789 --> 00:19:26,374
To be the chaperone!

286
00:19:27,917 --> 00:19:30,003
Mom! Ojie's nervous.

287
00:19:30,045 --> 00:19:33,298
He doesn't know what his father's like.

288
00:19:33,673 --> 00:19:36,509
Hey! You're the one who's nervous.

289
00:19:36,760 --> 00:19:40,430
You've nothing to worry about.
He's only Ojie's father!

290
00:19:40,472 --> 00:19:46,061
Maya's afraid, my father won't
like her tagging along.

291
00:19:46,644 --> 00:19:49,397
Mom, does he know you have another child?

292
00:19:49,439 --> 00:19:50,106
Yes of course!

293
00:19:50,190 --> 00:19:51,691
You told him?

294
00:19:51,733 --> 00:19:52,859
Why not?

295
00:19:52,901 --> 00:19:54,486
See? She told him!

296
00:19:54,861 --> 00:19:59,741
Maya said my father might not like her

297
00:19:59,783 --> 00:20:01,826
because she's not his daughter.

298
00:20:02,327 --> 00:20:08,708
Ojie's asking if his father loves him,
how come he hasn't visited him before?

299
00:20:08,750 --> 00:20:11,378
Poor Raffy, you both think ill of him!

300
00:20:11,419 --> 00:20:14,964
You haven't even met him yet
and you're already judging the man.

301
00:20:15,006 --> 00:20:18,093
Why don't you get to know him first?

302
00:20:18,343 --> 00:20:19,427
Approve?

303
00:20:19,469 --> 00:20:20,261
Approve!

304
00:20:52,252 --> 00:20:53,003
Hi.

305
00:20:54,671 --> 00:20:55,422
This is Ojie.

306
00:20:56,506 --> 00:20:58,133
And this is Maya.

307
00:20:59,634 --> 00:21:00,468
Ojie...

308
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:02,929
He's your father.

309
00:21:11,104 --> 00:21:11,855
Hi.

310
00:21:55,982 --> 00:21:57,233
How are you, really?

311
00:21:58,318 --> 00:21:59,861
Are you happy?

312
00:22:01,696 --> 00:22:02,489
Sometimes.

313
00:22:03,531 --> 00:22:05,492
Sometimes? Why not always?

314
00:22:07,035 --> 00:22:09,079
It's fine to be sad once in a while.

315
00:22:09,162 --> 00:22:11,289
We should also feel sad sometimes.

316
00:22:11,331 --> 00:22:13,958
So when you're happy, it's more meaningful.

317
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:16,169
In that sense, you are truly happy.

318
00:22:19,172 --> 00:22:22,425
Did you come back
because you got tired of Surigao?

319
00:22:22,717 --> 00:22:24,636
It's hard for Elinor.

320
00:22:26,388 --> 00:22:27,972
What about your work?

321
00:22:28,014 --> 00:22:30,642
When the baby comes, we'll go to America.

322
00:22:33,645 --> 00:22:34,437
Really?

323
00:22:35,188 --> 00:22:36,856
Yeah. New York.

324
00:22:40,276 --> 00:22:43,238
You've always said you hated living in the city.

325
00:22:43,279 --> 00:22:45,281
That you prefer living in a quiet town.

326
00:22:45,323 --> 00:22:46,991
What will you do in New York?

327
00:22:47,033 --> 00:22:47,992
No! Wait.

328
00:22:48,493 --> 00:22:52,580
What I said was,
I wanted to experience different places.

329
00:22:55,250 --> 00:22:56,042
Oh...

330
00:23:03,341 --> 00:23:04,634
I'm sorry...

331
00:23:05,468 --> 00:23:07,721
That things turned out this way for us.

332
00:23:07,762 --> 00:23:09,180
Don't talk like that!

333
00:23:09,222 --> 00:23:12,726
There's nothing wrong with our lives.
There's nothing to apologize for.

334
00:23:14,936 --> 00:23:16,771
She shivered in fright.

335
00:23:18,273 --> 00:23:20,066
The police were after us.

336
00:23:21,401 --> 00:23:24,612
The women ran with their children.

337
00:23:25,780 --> 00:23:27,949
My child couldn't move.

338
00:23:27,991 --> 00:23:29,784
She shivered in fright.

339
00:23:29,993 --> 00:23:30,660
Then -

340
00:23:30,702 --> 00:23:32,537
- My father doesn't shout!
- He does too!

341
00:23:32,579 --> 00:23:34,748
It's my father who doesn't shout!

342
00:23:34,789 --> 00:23:35,749
What's going on!

343
00:23:35,790 --> 00:23:38,543
How can you say your father doesn't shout?

344
00:23:38,585 --> 00:23:40,128
You don't even know him.

345
00:23:40,170 --> 00:23:41,755
I hate you! You're not my brother!

346
00:23:41,796 --> 00:23:44,299
You love your father more than mine.

347
00:23:44,341 --> 00:23:46,176
Of course, he's my father!
There's nothing you can do about it.

348
00:23:46,217 --> 00:23:47,302
He's my father!

349
00:23:47,552 --> 00:23:48,803
What's happening here?

350
00:23:48,845 --> 00:23:50,889
Tell your children to shut up!

351
00:23:51,348 --> 00:23:52,515
What's the problem?

352
00:23:52,557 --> 00:23:56,811
He said you love his father more than mine.

353
00:23:56,853 --> 00:23:59,147
Of course, he's her husband!

354
00:23:59,189 --> 00:24:00,231
You're so pesky!

355
00:24:00,315 --> 00:24:01,399
Wait, wait!

356
00:24:01,441 --> 00:24:02,817
Hold on a minute!

357
00:24:04,486 --> 00:24:06,613
I love them both, okay?

358
00:24:06,654 --> 00:24:08,782
You can't love them both!

359
00:24:09,032 --> 00:24:11,242
But, I do and I can't change that!

360
00:24:12,452 --> 00:24:14,913
Besides, with love...

361
00:24:15,663 --> 00:24:18,458
You don't divide love, you multiply it.

362
00:24:20,043 --> 00:24:22,003
Maya, please, stop it!

363
00:24:22,045 --> 00:24:23,463
Don't shout at the children!

364
00:24:23,546 --> 00:24:25,048
Don't shout at my mom!

365
00:24:25,090 --> 00:24:27,258
That's why she loves his dad more.

366
00:24:27,300 --> 00:24:30,011
You should have seen them embrace.

367
00:24:30,053 --> 00:24:31,763
They even kissed!

368
00:24:31,805 --> 00:24:32,847
See? I told you!

369
00:24:32,889 --> 00:24:36,142
That's right!
They were really sweet like newlyweds.

370
00:24:36,643 --> 00:24:38,687
You're such a turncoat!

371
00:24:40,188 --> 00:24:41,940
Do you even know what newlyweds look like?

372
00:24:41,981 --> 00:24:44,609
Don't change the topic.

373
00:24:45,235 --> 00:24:46,611
Did you kiss him?

374
00:24:47,112 --> 00:24:48,613
You should know Maya...

375
00:24:48,655 --> 00:24:53,076
Friends kiss each other, especially if they
haven't seen each other for a long time.

376
00:24:53,118 --> 00:24:55,453
You just saw each other yesterday!

377
00:24:56,454 --> 00:24:57,247
She's right!

378
00:24:58,832 --> 00:25:01,167
We were still uncomfortable with each other then!

379
00:25:01,209 --> 00:25:03,253
It's only today that we got to...

380
00:25:03,294 --> 00:25:04,170
Do what?

381
00:25:04,212 --> 00:25:05,588
Confess your love for each other?

382
00:25:05,630 --> 00:25:06,631
Oh, please!

383
00:25:06,881 --> 00:25:08,425
Not in front of the kids...

384
00:25:08,466 --> 00:25:09,050
So what?

385
00:25:09,092 --> 00:25:10,301
I thought there's nothing wrong with the truth?

386
00:25:10,343 --> 00:25:12,262
We didn't do anything wrong. So stop accusing me!

387
00:25:12,303 --> 00:25:13,638
You mean to say my daughter's a liar?

388
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:14,889
I never said that!

389
00:25:14,931 --> 00:25:16,975
All I said was that's not the truth!

390
00:25:17,017 --> 00:25:19,060
Ojie, are they fighting now?

391
00:25:54,846 --> 00:25:56,139
We're okay now right?

392
00:27:06,835 --> 00:27:08,253
Put something on.

393
00:27:08,294 --> 00:27:09,462
You'll catch a cold again.

394
00:27:47,709 --> 00:27:48,543
Hello?

395
00:27:51,713 --> 00:27:52,881
Hi. Raffy!

396
00:27:55,258 --> 00:27:56,551
Thank you.

397
00:27:58,928 --> 00:28:01,139
Why didn't you bring your daughter?

398
00:28:01,181 --> 00:28:02,307
That won't be a good idea.

399
00:28:02,349 --> 00:28:04,434
She might ask to stay here.

400
00:28:05,143 --> 00:28:07,270
I wonder what's taking Raffy so long.

401
00:28:07,312 --> 00:28:09,981
I could have done the grocery myself.

402
00:28:10,023 --> 00:28:11,691
Let him do it!

403
00:28:12,817 --> 00:28:14,611
He's used to doing it anyway.

404
00:28:15,111 --> 00:28:16,446
Really now?

405
00:28:16,488 --> 00:28:18,990
He claims he just started learning.

406
00:28:22,327 --> 00:28:24,454
My goodness, Raffy.

407
00:28:24,496 --> 00:28:28,750
It always takes him forever
but all he ever buys are canned goods.

408
00:28:28,792 --> 00:28:31,628
When we were together,
all we had were canned goods.

409
00:28:31,670 --> 00:28:33,213
I didn't like to cook.

410
00:28:35,006 --> 00:28:35,799
Really?

411
00:28:38,802 --> 00:28:40,637
Didn't he tell you about it?

412
00:28:43,556 --> 00:28:46,559
It's just, we never really got to talk about you.

413
00:28:50,063 --> 00:28:52,982
I'll wait for Dad outside, Mom.

414
00:28:53,024 --> 00:28:53,942
Sure.

415
00:28:53,983 --> 00:28:54,818
I'll go out now.

416
00:29:01,032 --> 00:29:03,326
This is hard for my son.

417
00:29:04,994 --> 00:29:07,831
It'll be the first time he'll be away from home.

418
00:29:08,832 --> 00:29:10,834
But this is his father's house.

419
00:29:12,585 --> 00:29:14,045
That's what I mean.

420
00:29:16,214 --> 00:29:18,258
It's his father's house...

421
00:29:19,384 --> 00:29:21,261
but it's not his home.

422
00:29:23,847 --> 00:29:25,348
The truth is...

423
00:29:26,141 --> 00:29:31,271
Even his own father isn't quite his father.

424
00:29:35,859 --> 00:29:37,819
My son's afraid you might not like him.

425
00:29:38,903 --> 00:29:43,158
He might do something you won't like.

426
00:29:45,702 --> 00:29:47,203
And if that were so,

427
00:29:48,747 --> 00:29:50,498
he might...

428
00:29:51,875 --> 00:29:55,587
He might lose the chance
to become close to his father.

429
00:29:58,048 --> 00:30:00,717
Is that why you chose to bring him over,

430
00:30:01,092 --> 00:30:03,428
instead of meeting Raffy somewhere else?

431
00:30:04,262 --> 00:30:06,556
To see me personally?

432
00:30:07,223 --> 00:30:11,227
To see whether I'm the type who beats children?

433
00:30:14,606 --> 00:30:16,274
I'm his mother.

434
00:30:18,777 --> 00:30:21,404
Mom, Dad's here!

435
00:30:22,030 --> 00:30:23,114
- Hi!
- Hi!

436
00:30:23,156 --> 00:30:25,533
- Hi!
- Sorry. It was so crowded at the supermarket.

437
00:30:25,658 --> 00:30:27,702
Here, I bought a lot of stuff.

438
00:30:28,119 --> 00:30:29,079
Where's Maya?

439
00:30:29,120 --> 00:30:30,789
She's with her dad.

440
00:30:31,122 --> 00:30:32,624
You should have brought her along.

441
00:30:32,665 --> 00:30:34,000
Come on, let's eat.

442
00:30:34,042 --> 00:30:35,168
No, don't bother!

443
00:30:35,210 --> 00:30:37,545
I'm afraid I can't stay longer. I have to go to the office.

444
00:30:37,629 --> 00:30:38,213
Bye!

445
00:30:39,506 --> 00:30:41,174
Call me anytime you want.

446
00:30:41,216 --> 00:30:41,758
Yes, Mom.

447
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:42,300
Elinor?

448
00:30:43,009 --> 00:30:45,470
Don't worry about Ojie. He'll be fine here.

449
00:30:46,930 --> 00:30:48,515
I'll see you to the door.

450
00:30:48,556 --> 00:30:49,849
Take care, Mom.

451
00:30:50,392 --> 00:30:52,686
Another one of our migrant workers

452
