along with you all day.

522
00:34:13,470 --> 00:34:15,472
I don't understand why you
had to leave Ojie there!

523
00:34:15,513 --> 00:34:17,307
You don't even care to know
what's happening to him!

524
00:34:17,349 --> 00:34:19,642
Maya, stop it already.
You're giving me a headache!

525
00:34:19,684 --> 00:34:20,602
I don't want to!

526
00:34:21,269 --> 00:34:24,439
Do you know what time it is? It's 9PM!

527
00:34:24,481 --> 00:34:28,276
The kid hasn't had dinner!
She should've eaten at 7!

528
00:34:28,318 --> 00:34:30,987
Will you never stop?
I'm losing my patience here!

529
00:34:31,029 --> 00:34:32,614
- Stop it!
- I don't want to!

530
00:34:32,655 --> 00:34:34,199
Here! I'll make dinner.

531
00:34:34,240 --> 00:34:36,284
You should have told me you'll be late!

532
00:34:36,326 --> 00:34:38,661
I could have prepared something!

533
00:34:38,703 --> 00:34:40,497
Then, she wouldn't be starving now!

534
00:34:40,538 --> 00:34:43,416
Really, Maya you don't plan to stop?!

535
00:34:43,458 --> 00:34:45,543
I'm really going to cover your mouth now!

536
00:34:45,585 --> 00:34:48,546
I'll cook some eggs. How do you want them done?

537
00:34:48,588 --> 00:34:51,758
You make so much noise! You can be a siren!

538
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:55,679
Did you hear me, Lea?!
What do I do with the eggs?!

539
00:34:55,720 --> 00:34:58,223
Well damn it! Make them hatch!

540
00:35:21,705 --> 00:35:23,456
How are you, Ojie?

541
00:35:24,791 --> 00:35:25,583
What?

542
00:35:25,917 --> 00:35:27,043
How are you?

543
00:35:28,837 --> 00:35:31,047
Does your Uncle Ding treat you well?

544
00:35:31,548 --> 00:35:32,674
Yeah.

545
00:35:35,719 --> 00:35:37,595
Like you're his own son?

546
00:35:41,558 --> 00:35:43,435
Yeah... sure.

547
00:35:43,893 --> 00:35:45,353
You sound unconvinced...

548
00:35:45,395 --> 00:35:46,771
No!

549
00:35:47,397 --> 00:35:49,232
I mean... yes!

550
00:35:50,358 --> 00:35:51,401
But...

551
00:35:53,361 --> 00:35:55,071
But sometimes it's hard.

552
00:35:56,531 --> 00:35:58,074
What do you mean?

553
00:35:59,993 --> 00:36:02,746
Knowing that I'm not really his son.

554
00:36:03,163 --> 00:36:03,830
Why?

555
00:36:03,872 --> 00:36:06,082
You mean, there's a gap between you two?

556
00:36:06,124 --> 00:36:08,043
You can't talk to him?

557
00:36:08,752 --> 00:36:10,420
When it's just us.

558
00:36:11,421 --> 00:36:14,424
When we're with other people,
I keep my distance.

559
00:36:14,799 --> 00:36:15,967
Especially before.

560
00:36:16,551 --> 00:36:17,552
Why?

561
00:36:18,470 --> 00:36:19,471
Well...

562
00:36:21,097 --> 00:36:22,098
Maybe because...

563
00:36:23,975 --> 00:36:26,519
People might think that I'm his son.

564
00:36:28,063 --> 00:36:30,523
What's wrong with that?

565
00:36:30,565 --> 00:36:32,150
Once...

566
00:36:33,026 --> 00:36:35,612
but this was a long time ago...

567
00:36:36,696 --> 00:36:39,783
Someone asked him how I was related to Mom.

568
00:36:40,617 --> 00:36:42,869
And he said, I was her nephew.

569
00:36:44,954 --> 00:36:47,457
But I'm not angry, Dad.

570
00:36:47,499 --> 00:36:49,876
Ding is nice to me.

571
00:36:49,918 --> 00:36:52,504
He doesn't even scold me.

572
00:36:53,546 --> 00:36:57,801
And I love Maya very much.

573
00:36:59,594 --> 00:37:02,639
Even if she's only my half sister,

574
00:37:03,598 --> 00:37:06,267
I won't exchange her for anything.

575
00:37:09,270 --> 00:37:11,064
The smoke is making my eyes sting.

576
00:37:23,451 --> 00:37:24,577
What is it?

577
00:37:29,165 --> 00:37:30,750
Is there anything wrong?

578
00:37:34,295 --> 00:37:35,380
Can we talk?

579
00:37:37,882 --> 00:37:39,175
About my son?

580
00:37:46,057 --> 00:37:47,851
What did you say?

581
00:37:49,519 --> 00:37:51,312
You heard me, Lei.

582
00:37:53,898 --> 00:37:57,527
I'm asking you if you'd consider
giving me the custody of Ojie.

583
00:37:58,319 --> 00:38:00,739
We'll take him with us to America.

584
00:38:02,490 --> 00:38:05,618
We won't be leaving until the baby comes though.

585
00:38:07,537 --> 00:38:09,998
So you have an entire year to think about it.

586
00:38:36,691 --> 00:38:40,236
Really now. It's nothing!

587
00:38:42,155 --> 00:38:46,159
Of course I'm not angry!
He's your son as much as he is mine!

588
00:38:46,826 --> 00:38:48,703
Don't worry about it.

589
00:38:49,204 --> 00:38:51,414
I don't mind at all.

590
00:38:53,208 --> 00:38:56,086
Besides, it's his decision anyway.

591
00:38:56,753 --> 00:38:59,756
Do you want to tell him yourself?
Or do you want me to do it?

592
00:39:00,715 --> 00:39:01,633
Ok...

593
00:39:01,675 --> 00:39:03,051
No problem.

594
00:39:03,385 --> 00:39:04,719
I'll do it for you.

595
00:39:04,761 --> 00:39:06,012
Okay, see you around!

596
00:39:06,638 --> 00:39:07,597
Bye!

597
00:39:29,452 --> 00:39:31,996
It's nice to have your mother by your side.

598
00:39:32,038 --> 00:39:34,791
She'll always be there
for you when things go wrong.

599
00:39:35,792 --> 00:39:38,712
She'll be there to kiss your pains away.

600
00:39:41,506 --> 00:39:43,383
On the other hand...

601
00:39:43,883 --> 00:39:47,721
There are some things
that are better to ask a father.

602
00:39:49,472 --> 00:39:54,561
Things that a father better understands.

603
00:39:58,106 --> 00:39:58,898
You know what...

604
00:39:59,315 --> 00:40:06,614
You'll go through feelings and experiences
that only a father can help you go through.

605
00:40:06,906 --> 00:40:08,116
Ugly!

606
00:40:12,120 --> 00:40:13,288
Ugly!

607
00:40:20,420 --> 00:40:23,840
We're not asking you to choose between us, Ojie.

608
00:40:25,550 --> 00:40:28,845
We're giving you the right
to make your own decision.

609
00:40:31,056 --> 00:40:33,641
So, think about your answer well.

610
00:40:38,772 --> 00:40:39,939
What's happening?

611
00:40:42,942 --> 00:40:44,861
I don't understand you!

612
00:40:46,446 --> 00:40:48,365
You've been crying for a month!

613
00:40:56,664 --> 00:40:58,875
What's wrong!?

614
00:41:03,880 --> 00:41:06,216
The teacher is right, Mrs. Gascon.

615
00:41:06,549 --> 00:41:11,054
Your children should have the same family name
if you want to pay the PTA fee once.

616
00:41:11,096 --> 00:41:13,306
What if they have different fathers?

617
00:41:13,890 --> 00:41:15,058
Why?

618
00:41:15,642 --> 00:41:17,977
Is your first husband dead?

619
00:41:18,770 --> 00:41:19,771
No.

620
00:41:21,690 --> 00:41:22,899
To whom are you married?

621
00:41:26,319 --> 00:41:27,237
To no one.

622
00:41:28,405 --> 00:41:29,948
Well how do I call you now?

623
00:41:31,032 --> 00:41:32,325
Call me Lea.

624
00:41:32,409 --> 00:41:35,161
That's what my children's fathers call me.

625
00:41:35,203 --> 00:41:36,413
Mrs. De Lara...

626
00:41:36,454 --> 00:41:38,039
Will you make up your mind?

627
00:41:38,081 --> 00:41:40,667
What do you really want to call me?

628
00:41:40,959 --> 00:41:45,422
Well I suggest that you transfer one
of your children to another school.

629
00:41:45,797 --> 00:41:47,799
Why Ms. Bustamante?

630
00:41:47,841 --> 00:41:50,093
So we can avoid a scandal!

631
00:41:50,427 --> 00:41:52,429
That would be good for you and for your children.

632
00:41:52,470 --> 00:41:55,348
Don't you go telling me
what's good for my children!

633
00:41:55,390 --> 00:41:57,976
- Look Ms.-
- There's nothing wrong with my children!

634
00:41:58,018 --> 00:41:59,561
Maybe there's something wrong with you!

635
00:41:59,602 --> 00:42:02,063
- Listen to me-
- No you listen to me!

636
00:42:02,105 --> 00:42:04,065
You want to expel one of my children?

637
00:42:04,107 --> 00:42:05,567
Go ahead! Do it!

638
00:42:05,984 --> 00:42:10,113
But know that DECS
and the courts will hear about it!

639
00:42:10,989 --> 00:42:13,908
I will not allow you to discriminate
my children, Mrs. Zalamea.

640
00:42:13,950 --> 00:42:16,119
And you'd better believe that.

641
00:42:40,352 --> 00:42:41,478
Bye, Mom!

642
00:42:49,986 --> 00:42:51,154
Dad!

643
00:42:51,780 --> 00:42:53,365
What took you so long?

644
00:42:54,366 --> 00:42:55,992
This is hard for me as well.

645
00:42:57,827 --> 00:43:00,080
Everytime Raffy takes Ojie...

646
00:43:01,039 --> 00:43:02,582
I feel sorry for my daughter.

647
00:43:02,665 --> 00:43:04,376
She misses her brother.

648
00:43:04,626 --> 00:43:07,295
Why not tell Raffy not to take Ojie so often?

649
00:43:07,796 --> 00:43:10,423
How can I deny my son
the chance to be with his father?

650
00:43:13,259 --> 00:43:16,388
It scares me sometimes, though.

651
00:43:17,389 --> 00:43:19,557
Everytime Raffy takes Ojie...

652
00:43:21,142 --> 00:43:23,853
I feel like I'm slowly losing my son.

653
00:43:25,355 --> 00:43:28,233
Wow, we're talking serious, man!

654
00:43:29,484 --> 00:43:34,906
I bet the next thing that'll come out
of your mouth will be pure rubbish!

655
00:44:10,275 --> 00:44:11,484
Hello!

656
00:44:11,693 --> 00:44:13,778
Johnny, you awake?

657
00:44:13,820 --> 00:44:15,822
No, no... It's not an emergency.

658
00:44:15,864 --> 00:44:18,742
It's about my son's school project...

659
00:44:21,578 --> 00:44:22,495
A radio?

660
00:44:22,537 --> 00:44:25,790
You called me up in the dead
of the night to ask about a radio?

661
00:44:25,832 --> 00:44:28,668
You could have just bought one!
Why do you have to make one?

662
00:44:28,710 --> 00:44:30,295
I said I'm sorry!

663
00:44:30,337 --> 00:44:33,965
It's for my son's project!
What can I do if the project requires -

664
00:44:40,096 --> 00:44:41,848
I'm back...

665
00:44:43,350 --> 00:44:45,435
This time it's for real.

666
00:44:54,569 --> 00:44:56,529
It gets more and more violent!

667
00:45:00,283 --> 00:45:03,370
All because of these evaluations!

668
00:45:05,705 --> 00:45:09,000
He's got all these creditors running after him.

669
00:45:16,132 --> 00:45:18,218
I don't want to go back to him, ever!

670
00:45:18,843 --> 00:45:20,053
I don't want to go back.

671
00:45:20,762 --> 00:45:23,223
I don't ever want to go back

672
00:45:24,140 --> 00:45:25,350
Ever!

673
00:45:25,392 --> 00:45:26,351
Sister...

674
00:45:26,976 --> 00:45:29,187
It's possible my mother may change her mind.

675
00:45:30,063 --> 00:45:31,815
But not me.

676
00:45:35,235 --> 00:45:37,654
I want out of this family!

677
00:45:46,788 --> 00:45:47,580
For you...

678
00:45:47,622 --> 00:45:48,790
Call Ojie.

679
00:45:48,832 --> 00:45:50,250
Tell him I'm home.

680
00:45:50,333 --> 00:45:52,002
He's not here.

681
00:45:52,585 --> 00:45:53,795
What?

682
00:45:56,131 --> 00:45:57,382
Mom...

683
00:45:57,632 --> 00:46:00,385
I think I have to tell you this...

684
00:46:00,427 --> 00:46:02,429
Ojie has been going out every night.

685
00:46:02,470 --> 00:46:06,474
He has been skipping school
and he's always playing billiards.

686
00:46:08,727 --> 00:46:12,939
What time it is? I'm running
out of luck and I'm hungry!

687
00:46:14,357 --> 00:46:15,567
Who's turn is it?

688
00:46:15,817 --> 00:46:18,653
Is it my turn? Alright! I'll finish this!

689
00:46:22,991 --> 00:46:27,203
Do you know what gambling does to people's lives?

690
00:46:27,287 --> 00:46:29,789
Once you get hooked, there's no turning back!

691
00:46:30,123 --> 00:46:32,000
It'll ruin your life!

692
00:46:32,042 --> 00:46:33,960
You'll destroy your life!

693
00:46:34,002 --> 00:46:35,295
You don't have to shout at him!

694
00:46:35,337 --> 00:46:37,172
I'm not talking to you!

695
00:46:37,213 --> 00:46:39,966
But you always do what you want.

696
00:46:40,425 --> 00:46:42,218
Why can't we?

697
00:46:46,097 --> 00:46:47,766
I'm not doing anything wrong!

698
00:46:47,807 --> 00:46:49,768
That's what you think!

699
00:46:49,809 --> 00:46:51,936
But, you're wrong! You're wrong!

700
00:47:04,866 --> 00:47:05,367
Ojie...

701
00:47:05,450 --> 00:47:06,534
Ojie! Ojie!

702
00:47:06,576 --> 00:47:06,951
Ojie!

703
00:47:08,244 --> 00:47:09,037
Ojie...

704
00:47:09,788 --> 00:47:10,246
Ojie! Ojie!

705
00:47:12,040 --> 00:47:12,832
Ojie...

706
00:47:13,667 --> 00:47:14,501
Ojie...

707
00:47:16,795 --> 00:47:17,295
Ojie...

708
00:47:18,755 --> 00:47:19,255
Ojie!

709
00:47:30,558 --> 00:47:32,727
I'm sorry to bother you, Uncle Johnny.

710
00:47:33,645 --> 00:47:35,105
It's okay.

711
00:47:36,106 --> 00:47:42,987
I can't call my father because
Grandma will take it against Mom.

712
00:47:43,029 --> 00:47:44,906
Because you see,

713
00:47:45,407 --> 00:47:49,953
Ojie wasn't able to attend this Boy Scout thing...

714
00:47:49,994 --> 00:47:52,122
because he had to bring a father along.

715
00:47:52,163 --> 00:47:54,624
He tried to call his dad...

716
00:47:54,666 --> 00:47:56,584
but he was away and didn't return his call.

717
00:47:56,626 --> 00:48:00,380
He didn't want to ask my Dad
because he's not his father anyway.

718
00:48:00,422 --> 00:48:04,426
So, he told his teacher that
he didn't want to join the Boy Scouts...

719
00:48:04,509 --> 00:48:07,095
but that's not true because it's his dream.

720
00:48:20,650 --> 00:48:23,987
You should have told me
about this Boy Scout ceremony.

721
00:48:28,408 --> 00:48:30,827
Even if you're father isn't here...

722
00:48:30,869 --> 00:48:32,662
I am.

723
00:48:39,252 --> 00:48:42,839
I could have tied the Boy Scout
kerchief around your neck...

724
00:48:46,051 --> 00:48:48,470
I can be a father too.

725
00:48:55,101 --> 00:48:57,437
But please...

726
00:48:59,522 --> 00:49:04,277
don't blame me for your father's shortcomings.

727
00:49:10,784 --> 00:49:13,578
Don't take out on me things
I can't do anything about.

728
00:49:25,215 --> 00:49:26,549
Mom...

729
00:49:34,349 --> 00:49:36,351
Mom, I'm sorry.

730
00:49:58,415 --> 00:50:00,375
I'm sorry too, son.

731
00:50:14,472 --> 00:50:16,307
Hey! Close your eyes.

732
00:50:16,349 --> 00:50:17,809
Don't peep!

733
00:50:17,851 --> 00:50:19,477
I don't like cheating.

734
00:50:24,858 --> 00:50:26,401
Hold on...

735
00:50:28,611 --> 00:50:29,154
Okay...

736
00:50:29,571 --> 00:50:31,114
Open your eyes!

737
00:50:32,365 --> 00:50:33,324
Wow!

738
00:50:33,575 --> 00:50:34,617
Is this ours, Mom?

739
00:50:34,659 --> 00:50:35,660
It's all yours.

740
00:50:35,702 --> 00:50:38,413
Just be careful. Be very very careful.

741
00:50:38,455 --> 00:50:39,497
We'll try it out now!

742
00:50:39,539 --> 00:50:40,749
Go ahead. Be careful though!

743
00:50:40,790 --> 00:50:41,875
Let's play, Ojie!

744
00:50:43,209 --> 00:50:45,670
I said be careful! Stay close!

745
00:50:46,212 --> 00:50:48,256
So now, you say 'be careful'!

746
00:50:48,298 --> 00:50:50,800
But you buy them a bike, knowing it's dangerous.

747
00:50:50,842 --> 00:50:53,261
That's nothing but trouble!

748
00:50:58,308 --> 00:50:59,059
Hey!

749
00:50:59,601 --> 00:51:01,436
Not too fast!

750
00:51:02,520 --> 00:51:05,523
Wow, you both got good grades.

751
00:51:05,899 --> 00:51:10,904
Wow, Ojie! It's just the
1st quarter but look! An 80 and 85!

752
00:51:10,945 --> 00:51:13,114
- Good!
- Mom, you must be mistaken.

753
00:51:13,782 --> 00:51:15,909
Those must be my grades.

754
00:51:16,284 --> 00:51:16,785
Yikes!

755
00:51:17,577 --> 00:51:19,496
I became a De Lara!

756
00:51:19,537 --> 00:51:21,581
Mom, mine's Gascon!

757
00:51:23,041 --> 00:51:24,042
Yikes!

758
00:51:26,753 --> 00:51:31,716
The different surnames of my children
must be quite confusing for you.

759
00:51:34,052 --> 00:51:35,679
Well at this point...

760
00:51:36,096 --> 00:51:38,181
I have already accepted your situation.

761
00:51:39,766 --> 00:51:40,892
There.

762
00:51:40,934 --> 00:51:42,644
One for each teacher.

763
00:51:43,186 --> 00:51:44,312
Thank you.

764
00:51:44,813 --> 00:51:47,190
You have to pay for those cards.

765
00:51:48,942 --> 00:51:51,945
No not to me, to the cashier.

766
00:51:55,073 --> 00:51:56,741
Ms. Bustamante,

767
00:51:56,783 --> 00:51:59,744
you're going to meet
the teachers of your children.

768
00:51:59,786 --> 00:52:02,080
Since you seem to have extra money,

769
00:52:02,122 --> 00:52:04,457
you might want to make
a contribution for the dead.

770
00:52:05,000 --> 00:52:09,796
There's nothing funny about a gruesome death, Ms. Bustamante.

771
00:52:16,803 --> 00:52:19,556
He's the father of your daughter's classmate.

772
00:52:19,597 --> 00:52:21,766
Their house was set on fire.

773
00:52:25,020 --> 00:52:29,107
You didn't know that a fire
broke out near here last Saturday ?

774
00:52:29,899 --> 00:52:30,984
Fire?

775
00:52:31,026 --> 00:52:32,736
Yes, fire!

776
00:52:32,777 --> 00:52:34,320
As in 'fire'.

777
00:52:34,362 --> 00:52:36,239
The squatters' area was burned down.

778
00:52:36,322 --> 00:52:39,617
Of course, no one will claim responsibility for it.

779
00:52:40,076 --> 00:52:45,665
But if you know your history,
this has been going on for quite some time.

780
00:52:45,832 --> 00:52:48,960
Especially when the government
wants to drive them away.

781
00:52:49,961 --> 00:52:55,884
Soliman, the one who died, thought
one of his children was left inside.

782
00:52:55,925 --> 00:52:58,053
He braved the fire and went back in.

783
00:52:58,094 --> 00:53:00,096
But the fire already spread.

784
00:53:00,138 --> 00:53:01,890
He couldn't get out anymore.

785
00:53:02,682 --> 00:53:05,935
Now, Ms. Bustamante, tell me if that's funny.

786
00:53:07,395 --> 00:53:08,605
I'm sorry.

787
00:53:09,022 --> 00:53:10,565
You should be.

788
00:53:12,859 --> 00:53:15,737
I wonder, why wasn't it featured in the papers?

789
00:53:17,280 --> 00:53:18,740
Why?

790
00:53:18,782 --> 00:53:22,702
Since when were poor people
like Soliman given importance?

791
00:53:28,041 --> 00:53:32,420
Can you help me get some details like...

792
00:53:33,505 --> 00:53:34,964
the number of families affected,

793
00:53:35,048 --> 00:53:36,800
where have they been relocated,

794
00:53:36,966 --> 00:53:38,718
and whether the government is doing anything.

795
00:53:39,135 --> 00:53:40,637
What for?

796
00:53:41,137 --> 00:53:43,223
To call the attention of the authorities...

797
00:53:43,848 --> 00:53:45,433
The NGOs...

798
00:53:45,475 --> 00:53:47,602
The proper government agencies.

799
00:53:48,269 --> 00:53:49,229
Why?

800
00:53:49,270 --> 00:53:51,106
Do you have any connections?

801
00:53:53,733 --> 00:53:56,111
I work for a non-government agency.

802
00:53:57,696 --> 00:54:00,448
Women in Crisis Center to be exact.

803
00:54:03,493 --> 00:54:05,036
I never realized...

804
00:54:05,078 --> 00:54:06,246
I know you don't.

805
00:54:07,080 --> 00:54:09,124
I always thought that...

806
00:54:10,041 --> 00:54:11,418
That, well...

807
00:54:11,459 --> 00:54:13,837
That you were, you know...

808
00:54:14,587 --> 00:54:16,047
A hospitality girl.

809
00:54:16,089 --> 00:54:18,091
I can believe that.

