You have only one father, too! Me!

1327
01:33:55,218 --> 01:34:01,599
Dad, I can't leave Mom
for all the grandmas in the world.

1328
01:34:01,641 --> 01:34:03,643
And come to think of it,
I don't even like grandma.

1329
01:34:03,685 --> 01:34:05,895
What if you won't see me anymore?

1330
01:34:06,688 --> 01:34:10,191
No problem.
I have a lot of your pictures anyway!

1331
01:34:11,901 --> 01:34:13,653
You're so hard to talk to.

1332
01:34:13,695 --> 01:34:18,324
You can get mad at me if you want to.
I still won't leave my mom.

1333
01:34:18,366 --> 01:34:20,535
She's my mother!

1334
01:34:23,413 --> 01:34:25,832
No, Dad. It's not because
no one will take care of her.

1335
01:34:26,291 --> 01:34:29,210
Mom has lots of friends.

1336
01:34:29,294 --> 01:34:33,089
And besides, that's not the reason.

1337
01:34:33,131 --> 01:34:37,844
It's just that I don't want
to lose my mom nor my sister.

1338
01:34:56,321 --> 01:34:57,906
Are you angry?

1339
01:35:00,867 --> 01:35:03,328
No, I'm not.

1340
01:35:04,204 --> 01:35:07,123
You understand, right?

1341
01:35:09,542 --> 01:35:12,962
I really like Auntie Elinor.

1342
01:35:13,963 --> 01:35:16,841
But she's not my mother.

1343
01:35:35,860 --> 01:35:37,946
The problem is solved, Mom.

1344
01:35:37,987 --> 01:35:40,323
We already told both our fathers.

1345
01:35:40,573 --> 01:35:43,201
We won't go with them.

1346
01:35:43,660 --> 01:35:47,497
We won't exchange you for anything in this world.

1347
01:35:59,050 --> 01:36:01,261
Happy Women's Day, Mom.

1348
01:36:01,302 --> 01:36:04,097
We love you very much.

1349
01:36:25,410 --> 01:36:27,704
Do you regret anything about your life?

1350
01:36:28,621 --> 01:36:31,791
Me? About you and Ding?

1351
01:36:32,208 --> 01:36:35,712
Without you, I won't have my children.

1352
01:36:38,506 --> 01:36:40,842
Do you still love Ding?

1353
01:36:42,802 --> 01:36:45,680
You also want to ask whether
I still love you, right?

1354
01:36:47,307 --> 01:36:50,602
My answer is yes. I love you and I love him...

1355
01:36:51,311 --> 01:36:54,064
It's not that easy to understand
but it's the way it is.

1356
01:36:55,023 --> 01:36:58,234
If you love me, why did we end up like this?

1357
01:36:58,276 --> 01:37:01,112
Why didn't you come with me when I had to leave?

1358
01:37:02,030 --> 01:37:05,158
Why did you leave when I couldn't go with you?

1359
01:37:07,494 --> 01:37:10,997
Because we are two independent people...

1360
01:37:13,541 --> 01:37:16,336
Who wanted to do different things.

1361
01:37:23,218 --> 01:37:25,178
I lost you.

1362
01:37:27,514 --> 01:37:30,684
But if I clung on to you...

1363
01:37:31,101 --> 01:37:33,812
I would have lost myself.

1364
01:37:34,521 --> 01:37:38,108
How can you live with someone
who has lost her identity?

1365
01:37:38,149 --> 01:37:41,027
She'll never make a good wife.

1366
01:37:46,783 --> 01:37:49,619
Why did you ask me out?

1367
01:37:51,246 --> 01:37:52,288
No reason.

1368
01:37:52,831 --> 01:37:56,126
To say goodbye. Elinor and I are leaving.

1369
01:38:00,755 --> 01:38:03,508
Take care of the children, Lei.

1370
01:38:04,384 --> 01:38:06,928
And yourself too.

1371
01:38:11,141 --> 01:38:13,685
Are you happy, Raf?

1372
01:38:14,477 --> 01:38:16,271
Sometimes.

1373
01:38:23,737 --> 01:38:26,698
Do you understand, Raf?

1374
01:38:28,491 --> 01:38:32,537
That I won't ever be sorry
for anything in my life?

1375
01:38:33,246 --> 01:38:37,417
Not to you and not to anyone.

1376
01:38:38,168 --> 01:38:41,087
There's nothing to be sorry for.

1377
01:38:56,519 --> 01:39:00,732
Can you lend me just one more day of your life?

1378
01:39:00,774 --> 01:39:03,568
Let's give each other just one more day.

1379
01:39:03,610 --> 01:39:05,653
What will we do?

1380
01:39:05,695 --> 01:39:07,322
Anything!

1381
01:39:07,781 --> 01:39:11,201
Let's go to the places where we used to go...

1382
01:39:11,284 --> 01:39:13,495
Eat the food we used to share...

1383
01:39:13,536 --> 01:39:15,872
Drink from a single glass...

1384
01:39:15,914 --> 01:39:18,792
Swap stories, laugh together...

1385
01:39:19,417 --> 01:39:22,837
Dream and make memories.

1386
01:39:25,548 --> 01:39:26,800
Please, Raf?

1387
01:39:28,301 --> 01:39:32,055
Let's be crazy even just for a day!

1388
01:40:26,901 --> 01:40:29,529
Thank you.

1389
01:41:16,826 --> 01:41:20,246
I can't think of anything to say.

1390
01:41:27,921 --> 01:41:33,760
I can only think that not too long ago,
when Ojie was younger...

1391
01:41:35,053 --> 01:41:39,933
He was asking me how babies are made.

1392
01:41:43,144 --> 01:41:48,024
He stopped asking me that question.
Perhaps he has learned the answer.

1393
01:41:48,942 --> 01:41:51,069
Now you know the answer, Ojie!

1394
01:41:55,949 --> 01:41:59,536
But then, that question can easily be answered.

1395
01:42:01,162 --> 01:42:03,331
What's harder to answer...

1396
01:42:04,040 --> 01:42:13,008
Is how can children grow up
to become decent human beings.

1397
01:42:16,011 --> 01:42:21,641
For if every child were molded in such a way,

1398
01:42:22,517 --> 01:42:27,397
then we would have a just
and decent society by now.

1399
01:42:27,439 --> 01:42:30,942
One that we can proudly pass on to you.

1400
01:42:35,280 --> 01:42:38,074
But we are still trying hard to achieve this.

1401
01:42:38,116 --> 01:42:42,620
Anything that can be done
to prepare a better future for you.

1402
01:42:43,830 --> 01:42:49,669
Many of us try to make a better world for you.

1403
01:42:50,086 --> 01:42:52,630
For all of us!

1404
01:42:56,801 --> 01:43:02,057
To all of you, parents and children alike...

1405
01:43:03,099 --> 01:43:08,104
May you have a wonderful journey
of reaching for the stars!
